occurrences.line_text: Of that same hornes great vertues weren told,
Whose sides with dapled circles weren dight;
About her shoulders weren loosely shed,
And furious fits at earst quite weren quaild:
Therein an hundred raunges weren pight,
For by those vgly formes weren pourtrayd,
Eftsoones long waxen torches weren light,
And in those Tapets weren fashioned
About the which two Serpents weren wound,
Whose yuorie shoulders weren couered all,
Vpon our way, to which we weren bent,
Still Vre, swift Werfe, and Oze the most of might,
Her name was Agape whose children werne
